%N A397730 a(n) is the number of distinct triples of triangles chosen from n^2 unit triangles of a triangular grid up to rotation such that no two triangles share common side.
%C A397730 Triples containing any of the following pairs of triangles, denoted by their centers are removed to avoid triangles sharing common sides: (h,k) and (h+1,k+1), (h,k) and (h-2,k+1), (h,k) and (h+1,k-2).
%H A397730 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A397730/b397730.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100</a>
%H A397730 Janaka Rodrigo, <a href="/A397730/a397730.txt">Python code</a>
%F A397730 Conjectured g.f. x^2 * (1+7*x+52*x^2+42*x^3+28*x^4-10*x^5-x^6+x^7) / ((1+x+x^2) * (1-x)^7). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 14 2026
%e A397730 n = 3 has following triples of triangles: {(1,1),(1,4),(1,7)}, {(1,1),(1,4),(4,1)}, {(1,1),(1,4),(4,4)}, {(1,1),(1,4),(5,2)}, {(1,1),(1,4),(7,1)}, {(1,1),(1,7),(4,1)}, {(1,1),(2,5),(4,1)}, {(1,1),(1,7),(5,2)}, {(1,1),(1,7),(7,1)}, {(1,1),(2,5),(4,1)}, {(1,1),(2,5),(5,2)}, {(1,1),(4,1),(4,4)}, {(2,2),(2,5),(5,2)}.
%e A397730 Therefore, a(3) = 13.
